{"title_page": "University of West Yangon", "text_new": "{{short description|Liberal arts and sciences university in Myanmar}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name         = West Yangon University (WYU)\n| native_name  = \u101b\u1014\u103a\u1000\u102f\u1014\u103a \u1021\u1014\u1031\u102c\u1000\u103a\u1015\u102d\u102f\u1004\u103a\u1038 \u1010\u1000\u1039\u1000\u101e\u102d\u102f\u101c\u103a\n| image        = WYU Logo.png\n| motto        = To develop the knowledge for benefit of the country\n| established  = {{start date and age|27 June 2002}}\n| location     = [[Htantabin Township|Htantabin]] 11393 <br>[[Yangon Division]], Myanmar\n| coor         = {{coord|16|56|50|N|96|00|54|E|display=title|type:edu}}\n| type         = Government\n| rector       = Tin Maung Tun<ref name=\"Convocation Record\">{{cite book|last=WYU|first=Convocation Record|title=List of AB Members|year=2012|publisher=West Yangon University, Universities' Press|location=Yangon|pages=50}}</ref>\n| students     = 22,448 (2019)<ref name=\"news letter of wyu\">{{cite news | last=wyu| title=News Letter distributed by Rector | date=2012-11-12 | publisher=WYU Administration Section}}</ref>\n| undergrad    = BA, BSc, BA (Hons;), BSc (Hons;)\n| postgrad     = MA, MSc, MRes\n| website      = {{url|wyu.moe.edu.mm}}\n| affiliations = \n}}\n\nThe '''University of West Yangon''' ({{lang-my|\u101b\u1014\u103a\u1000\u102f\u1014\u103a \u1021\u1014\u1031\u102c\u1000\u103a\u1015\u102d\u102f\u1004\u103a\u1038 \u1010\u1000\u1039\u1000\u101e\u102d\u102f\u101c\u103a}} {{IPA-my|j\u00e0\u0270\u0303\u0261\u00f2\u028a\u0270\u0303 \u0294\u0259na\u028a\u0294p\u00e1\u026a\u0270\u0303 t\u025b\u0294k\u0259\u03b8\u00f2|}}), located in [[Htantabin, Yangon Division]], is a [[liberal arts]] and [[sciences]] university in Myanmar. The university offers bachelor's and master's degrees in liberal arts and science.<ref name=finite>{{cite web | url=http://www.finitesite.com/sanchaung2/colleges.html | title=List of Colleges and Universities in and around Yangon | accessdate=2008-12-20 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090109071322/http://www.finitesite.com/sanchaung2/colleges.html | archivedate=2009-01-09 }}</ref> Students who wish to pursue post-graduate (especially PhD) studies typically go to [[Yangon University]].\n\n==Degrees==\nClassified as an '''Arts and Science''' university in the Burmese university education system, West Yangon University \noffers bachelor's and master's degree in common liberal arts and sciences disciplines. Its ordinary [[Bachelor of Arts]] (BA) and [[Bachelor of Science]] (BSc) take four years to complete, honours degrees BA (Hons) and BSc (Hons) take five years and master's degrees MA, MSc and MRes take seven and eight years.<ref name=finite/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!width=\"150\"|'''Program'''\n!width=\"100\"|'''Bachelor's'''\n!width=\"75\"|'''Master's'''\n!width=\"50\"|'''Doctorate'''\n!width=\"150\"|'''Head of the Department'''<ref name=\"Convocation Record\"/>\n|-\n| [[Myanmar language|Myanmar]]\n| BA, BA (Hons;)\n| MA, MRes\n| \n|Daw Khin Pale\n|-\n| [[English language|English]]\n| BA, BA (Hons;)\n| MA\n|PhD\n|Mi Mi Gyee\n|-\n| [[Geography]]\n| BA, BA (Hons;)\n| MA\n|\n|Daw Khin Mya Thway\n|-\n| [[History]]\n| BA, BA (Hons;)\n| MA, MRes\n|\n|Thida Myint\n|-\n| [[Philosophy]]\n| BA, BA (Hons;)\n| MA, MRes\n|\n|Thet Thet Naing\n|-\n| [[Oriental Studies]]\n| BA, BA (Hons;)\n| MA, MRes\n|\n|Kyu Kyu Hla\n|-\n| [[Geology]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc\n|\n|Myo Thant\n|-\n| [[Botany]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc, MRes\n|\n|Myat Thida\n|-\n| [[Chemistry]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc, MRes\n|\n|Hlaing Hlaing Oo\n|-\n| [[Mathematics]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc, MRes\n|\n|Moe Thuzar\n|-\n| [[Physics]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc, MRes\n|\n|Dr Tin Tin Win\n|-\n| [[Zoology]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc,\n|\n|Thet Thet Win\n|-\n| [[Industrial Chemistry]]\n| BSc, BSc (Hons;)\n| MSc, MRes\n|\n|Khin Htwe Nyunt\n|-\n| [[Law]]\n| LLB (UDE)\n| \n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Refere